{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"06d268da-4be8-477f-ae5f-738cf718575d","content":"The migration is straightforward. In your project file, simply **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove this line (or set to false): -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n### What this changes\n\n| | VSTest (`true`) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform (default) |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Runner** | `vstest.console` / `dotnet test` adapter | Built-in test host |\n| **CLI** | `dotnet test` still works | `dotnet test` still works (also supports running the test exe directly) |\n\n### Additional things to check\n\n1. **`dotnet test`** — works with both runners; no command changes needed.\n2. **CI / args** — if you pass VSTest-specific args (e.g., `-- RunConfiguration.TestSessionTimeout=...`), replace them with the [Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform-overview).\n3. **`.runsettings`** — still supported, but some settings may differ.\n4. **Test Explorer in VS** — works in VS 17.10+ with Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nSince MSTest.Sdk **3.4+** defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is the only required change.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cec4916f-4d1e-4e35-a0a7-4bbc3a000aef","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty and doesn't contain any relevant files. This is a general knowledge question about MSTest migration. Let me answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":421,"requestId":"6800:228DD8:2A4BE06:2E93A42:69FD3465"},"id":"d289e817-9014-4c11-ad9a-c770c3625806","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:55:11.758Z","parentId":"fa649efa-52ce-4a45-93b6-cc7d133f3bd5"}
